gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Spurs 130, Knicks 126
gameRecap.excerpt: San Antonio defeats New York in OT, 130-126. For San Antonio, Victor Wembanyama led the way with a career-high 40 points, 20 rebounds, and seven assists. Jalen Brunson finished with a new career high 61 points (five 3PM), four rebounds, and six assists while aided by Donte DiVincenzo setting a new franchise record for 3PM (242) in a season and recording 20 points (six 3PM) and six rebounds for New York in the losing effort. San Antonio improves to 18-56, while New York moves to 44-29 with the loss.
